dismissalText.commentary: David Miller lbw b Vitori 45 (48b 2x4 2x6 56m) SR: 93.75

dismissalComment.html: loud appeal for lbw and the finger's gone up! He got the yorker right this time on middle and leg, Miller came down a step and got hit on the shoe in front of middle and leg while trying to drive it on the on side but missed. Can't say for sure if it was out because of the angle, but looked very close in real time
one more, Williams gets his first wicket! He pitched it up and close to Abbott, not giving him much room and Abbott lofted it a little wide of long-on and Raza ran in to take another good catch

dismissalText.commentary: John Nyumbu c †de Kock b Imran Tahir 18 (18b 1x4 1x6 27m) SR: 100

commentTextItems.html: he was walking back to collect his sweater by the time the umpire finally agreed with him. Tahir was that certain this was out. Short ball turns big outside off, Nyumbu goes for a cut and feathers a bottom edge to the keeper

commentPostTextItems.html: So that's all we've got for you from Bulawayo. Firdose Moonda's report has already landed, so do check that out. The final game is on Thursday, so do join us then. For now though, this is Alagappan Muthu and Vishal Dikshit saying buh-bye..

Wayne Parnell is Man of the Match. "Every time you put on this jersey is special and to contribute for a win is massive. Fortunate to be in a position to bat and ball and fielding wise as well. Facing spin was very very difficult, some balls turned really big and Zimbabwe bowled smartly as well. Credit to myself and Abbo there to get us past 250. Obviously havent played in a couple of months but nice to be back. Can practice all you want, but to play out there in the middle is how you get back"

"Just as happy, bit of an awkward game with some of hte dismissals, specifically myself. Very happy with our recovery," says AB de Villiers. Hash didnt score many but the others did. We were very hungry in the field and that always helped. Very happy for Parny, with both bat and ball. Still havent figured why I ran, I sort of thought I was in the middle of a double. Then I head Faf's voice saying something like "oh my God, what're you doing". I felt 250-off was enough with out bowling atack, 280 was par so we didn't bat well. The top order failed but still we got that total. There might be a few changes, Hash has played a lot of games, possibly give him a rest and see what Rilee Rossow is all about. Marchant de Lange with his pace, We still want to win but maybe a couple of changes here and there"

"Very happy with the bowlers to restrict South Africa to 250, couldn't ask for more, but disappointing that we couldn't picked it up with the batting. Losing so many early wickets is criminal"Elton Chigumbura said. "The main thing was keeping wickets in hand. You can go at 10 per over in the last ten, but we lost too many early wickets and we couldn't pull it back. The only guy who played well for us was Sean Williams but he didn't have any support. Last chance now to make the departments to play well. Hopefully we can do better than these last few games"

5.15 pm So South Africa take the three-match series 2-0. The players troop off the field in good spirits to shake hands with the hosts. It was only the third time that Zimbabwe had bowled them out in 34 attempts, but the improvements in the bowling did not seep into their batting. The top-order did not offer much fight except for Sean Williams' gutsy fifty. Once they tumbled to 88 for 6, there was really no hope of a comeback. Yet the Bulawayo crowd had their fun, nothing would stamp out their spirit. It was fun watching them sing and dance, but the joy on the field was quite limited

commentTextItems.html: this is a lot slower, but Vitori is waiting on the back foot and the shortish delivery is cut away quite smartly behind point. That makes it 21 runs off the over!

headshotImage.caption: Brian Vitori player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Brian Vitori player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: bowls it even faster this time and Vitori just about gets an inside edge to it
two in a row! that's on the roof! Pushed through on leg stump and Vitori plants his front leg away and pummels another sweep shot. JP has a wry smile as he checks the hang time on that
rocks back and hammers a six over midwicket. Up comes a roar from Bulawayo. Poor ball from Duminy as he allowed the batsman enough time to line him up and smack him
launched to the long-on boundary! His eyes lit up at the flight on offer and held nothing back, Smote over mid-on's head and eventually dribbled to the boundary

commentPreTextItems.html: Two overs left, can Zimbabwe survive? It's JP Duminy

commentTextItems.html: tossed up outside off, he lunges forward and sweeps to deep midwicket
quicker and flatter googly, Vitori read it and cuts towards point. Not much conviction behind the shot, but then again he is a No.11

headshotImage.caption: Brian Vitori player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Brian Vitori player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: fires in a yorker on off stump, this time the batsman is alert enough

commentPreTextItems.html: Brian Vitori is the last man in

commentTextItems.html: googly straight up, lovely flight again. Vitori did not pick it as he went for the sweep and is beaten

dismissalText.commentary: Neville Madziva b Imran Tahir 25 (37b 4x4 0x6 43m) SR: 67.56

commentTextItems.html: got 'im! This was full and straight and he celebrates befitting his reputation. Punches the air and gives the departing batsman a stare. One sweep too many for Madziva
full toss on middle and leg, Nyumbu shovels it up in the air but it doesn't reach the man in the deep
loopy delivery that grips and turns and beats the batsman's intention of slugging him over the leg side. His back foot was inside the crease though so it didn't matter if de Kock didn't collect
swept away, quite strongly too but this shot is made by its placement. Kept well fine of deep square leg and the bowler's flatter trajectory only helped him
slammed down the ground, that time he advanced and made lots of room for himself to unleash a full swing of the arms
gets on top of the bounce and sweeps with the bat face closed so that it doesn't go up in the air towards short fine leg
gets down for a sweep as he sees this one flatter and angled in at him, doesn't connect and the ball wanders away off his pads. Appeal denied because that would miss leg
ventures down the track and pushes a good length ball back at the bowler
good length ball on off stump, Madziva goes right back in his crease to defend
goes for a googly, but it has been picked and Nyumbu cuts to point

headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Brian Vitori player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Brian Vitori player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ryan McLaren c Chigumbura b Vitori 4 (12b 0x4 0x6 30m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: the crowd goes berserk, another catch has been taken! He pitched it wide outside off and seeing the room, McLaren went for a big drive on the up and handed a simple catch straight to Chigumbura at cover point

dismissalText.commentary: Wayne Parnell c Williams b Madziva 24 (27b 2x4 0x6 39m) SR: 88.88

dismissalComment.html: lofts it down the ground again, this time it's going to long-off and Williams runs in a long away to take a great catch diving forward! It was full and outside off, Parnell couldn't get the middle of the bat and Williams got there just in time

dismissalText.commentary: Kyle Abbott c Sikandar Raza b Williams 23 (26b 2x4 0x6 32m) SR: 88.46

dismissalComment.html: one more, Williams gets his first wicket! He pitched it up and close to Abbott, not giving him much room and Abbott lofted it a little wide of long-on and Raza ran in to take another good catch

dismissalText.commentary: Aaron Phangiso c Nyumbu b Williams 2 (3b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: another good catch on the run from Zimbabwe in the deep, all over for South Africa! It was a short delivery asking to be put away and Phangiso pulled it in the air to deep midwicket where Nyumbu ran to his left to take it over his left shoulder

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza b Parnell 7 (24b 1x4 0x6 30m) SR: 29.16

dismissalComment.html: timberrr! Masakadza looked like he had it covered with a push down the ground, but there was gap between bat, which came down at an angle from gully, and pad and the inside edge pings into the stumps. Reward for bowling a good length for Parnell as leg stump cartwheels

dismissalText.commentary: Richmond Mutumbami lbw b Phangiso 12 (20b 0x4 1x6 27m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: guess AB knows better than me! This was the arm ball, skid on off the deck to smack Mutumbami below the knee-roll. Poor shot as he was looking to flick across the line. The closed bat face had no chance.

headshotImage.caption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza b McLaren 0 (14b 0x4 0x6 19m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: full, angled in, seaming further as well. Raza has not read that at all, he is surprised by the movement and has ended up offered the ball free passage onto his off stump

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor c Miller b Duminy 14 (28b 2x4 0x6 37m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: he flung his head down in disappointment the minute he met the ball. Raced down the track and perhaps got a little too close to it. Goes for the loft and forces it with a lot of bottom hand... right down long-on's throat

headshotImage.caption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams c Parnell b McLaren 55 (84b 3x4 2x6 103m) SR: 65.47

dismissalComment.html: he's holed out to mid-off! Slaps his bat down on his pad as he walks off. It was a similar ball, but this time he goes full-on with the drive and offers a simple catch to Parnell. A brave fight, and the only one from Zimbabwe's batsmen comes to an end

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Duminy b Parnell 7 (13b 0x4 0x6 24m) SR: 53.84

dismissalComment.html: bangs it in and Chigumbura hands a simple catch to mid-on! It was short and quick and rushed on to the batsman who pulled to put it away but only lobbed a sitter to Duminy. Parnell does a little jig for his second wicket

headshotImage.longCaption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022

headshotImage.longCaption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022

headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Luke Jongwe c Amla b McLaren 6 (16b 0x4 0x6 26m) SR: 37.5

dismissalComment.html: Amla takes it at slip! It was a short of length ball well outside off, Jongwe played it late to run it fine but it was too fine and Amla leapt to his right to take a low diving catch

dismissalText.commentary: Prosper Utseya lbw b Parnell 15 (34b 2x4 0x6 56m) SR: 44.11

dismissalComment.html: up comes the finger, the batsman was dancing down the track and then whipped across the line of a straight delivery. It was a yorker that hit him on off stump and might just have gone on to clatter leg. Utseya was rushing back, thinking he would have been given the benefit and topped the off bail when his bat tickled the stumps as well

dismissalText.commentary: Neville Madziva b Imran Tahir 25 (37b 4x4 0x6 43m) SR: 67.56

dismissalComment.html: got 'im! This was full and straight and he celebrates befitting his reputation. Punches the air and gives the departing batsman a stare. One sweep too many for Madziva

dismissalText.commentary: John Nyumbu c †de Kock b Imran Tahir 18 (18b 1x4 1x6 27m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: he was walking back to collect his sweater by the time the umpire finally agreed with him. Tahir was that certain this was out. Short ball turns big outside off, Nyumbu goes for a cut and feathers a bottom edge to the keeper
